FBIS4-3789 "drchi079_a_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-079 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Spokesman Restates Sovereignty Over Tibet Spokesman Restates Sovereignty Over Tibet OW2204190094 Beijing China Radio International in English to Western North America 0400 GMT 22 Apr 94 OW2204190094 Beijing China Radio International English BFN [Foreign Ministry Spokesman Wu Jianmin's Weekly Press Briefings; from the "Current Affairs" program] [Text] Finally, the Foreign Ministry spokesman restated China's sovereignty over Tibet. Wu Jianmin said the Central Government has made repeated contacts with personal representatives of the Dalai Lama, the spiritual leader of Tibet. Wu Jianmin said the door is always open for talks between the Central Government and the exiled Dalai Lama. However, he stressed, the talks can cover anything but Tibet's separation from the country.
